    "text": "The contradiction is resolved by separating the stage of method specification (admissibility) from the stage of conditional viability assessment (which includes maintainer, toolchain, content type, and plugin-architecture limits).",
    "topic": "Two-stage evaluation"
  },
  {
    "text": "The reconciled cross-reconstruction already treats admissibility as conditional on a defined method, while listing additional operational conditions; statement B incorrectly collapses admissibility into two operational factors.",
